HEADWORD: Sea-island
<hw>Sea"-is`land</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Of or pertaining
to certain islands along the coast of South Carolina and Georgia;
<as>as, <ex>sea-island</ex> cotton, a superior cotton of long fiber
produced on those islands</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

